verbs.description: outsling (third-person singular simple present outslings, present participle outslinging, simple past and past participle outslung)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To sling more effectively than; to surpass in slinging.
examples: As it now is, the enemy outshoot and outsling us so far that the Cretan archers and our javelineers cannot reach them.
And thundering engine murderous balls outsling
